          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Comparison of different methods for the determination",
                " of fission fragment velocity, mass, and energy distri-",
                " butions for Th-232(N,F)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "K.Th.Brinkmann",
                "J.Kiesewetter",
                "F.M.Baumann",
                "H.Freiesleben",
                "H.J.Lytke-Stetzkamp",
                "H.J.Paul",
                "H.G.Schwanke",
                "H.Sohlbach"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2GERBOC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "DYNAM"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERBOC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 4 MV dynamitron tandem accelerator,",
                " delivering an average proton current of 75 micro-amps."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-LI7"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A 100 micro-g/cm2 metallic lithium target with",
                " natural abundance, evaporated onto an aluminium hut of",
                " 16 mm diameter. The hut was water-cooled and served as",
                " a beam dump. The average neutron flux was 1.7e+07",
                " N/cm2 sec through the fissile deposit.",
                ".Two sets of measurements were performed. In the first",
                " the proton beam was defocussed to a diameter of 12 mm,",
                " giving an energy resolution of about +/-20 KeV. In the",
                " second the well-focussed proton beam was scanned over",
                " an area of 8 X 8 mm by deflection magnets, thus giving",
                " a better energy resolution."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   Three different methods were applied."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "   I. Double time-of-flight measurement of coincident",
                "      fission fragments.",
                "  Ii. Double energy measurement of coincident fission",
                "      fragments.",
                " Iii. Time-of-flight/energy measurements of single",
                "      fission fragments."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Fission fragments were detected with five",
                " 10.2 X 10.2 cm parallel plate avalanche counters,",
                " having a position resolution of +/-0.8 mm. They were",
                " placed at a distance of 40 cm from the target and at",
                " angles of 0, 45, +/-90, -107 and -135 degrees with",
                " respect to the proton beam direction. These detectors",
                " were used for method I and iii."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two 900 mm2 and three 300 mm2 F-series ortec",
                " surface barrier detectors measured time-of-flight and",
                " energy of the fragments. They were placed at angles of",
                " 17, 73, -107, -118 and - 148 degrees. These detectors",
                " were used for method ii and iii.",
                ".The time reference signal for all the detectors was",
                " provided by a one channel plate arrangement, placed",
                " perpendicular to the target out of the reaction plane.",
                " Electrons knocked out from the target were deflected",
                " to the detector with an electrostatic mirror. By the",
                " position read-out the reaction point in the target",
                " could be determined with a resolution of +/-1.5 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "98-CF-252(0,F),,KE,FF",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "98-CF-252(0,F),,KE,FF",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "98-CF-252(0,F)",
                        "target": "98-CF-252",
                        "projectile": "0",
                        "process": "F",
                        "product": "",
                        "quantity": ",KE,FF",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",KE,*"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".In the first set of measurements the fission target",
                " was stacked from four 140 micro-g/cm2 thf4 layers,",
                " each evaporated onto 25 micro-g/cm2 carbon foil. In",
                " the second set it was a face-to-face sandwich of two",
                " 510 micro-g/cm2 thf4 layers on 50 micro-g/cm2 carbon.",
                " The targets were located 42 mm from the neutron",
                " producing target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The data were corrected for energy losses in the",
                " target."
              ]
            }
          ],
